Boil a #large pot{} of water on high heat with 1/2 tsp of @salt{} for your rice. Rinse the
@Brown Basmati Rice{2%cups} under running water for ~{30%seconds} and then add to the
rapidly boiling water. Cook the rice for around ~{25%minutes} until it is soft then drain and
keep to the side and allow to cool slightly.

Peel and finely dice half the @Onion{1/2}(peeled and finely diced). Cut the
@Cherry Tomatoes{2}(quartered) into quarters. Roughly chop the @Coriander{1/2}(roughly chopped).
Rinse and drain the @Organic Black Beans{1/2%(drained)}.

Mix the @Smoked Paprika{2%tsp} with the zest of half the @Lime{1/2}(zested), 1/4 tsp of @salt{},
@Pepper{} and 1 tbsp of @olive oil{}. Cut the @British Chicken Thighs{6} into bite sized
pieces and coat in the spice mix.

Heat a #frying pan{} over a medium-high heat with 2 tsp of @olive oil{} and cook the
@Diced Chorizo{1/4%cup} and onion for ~{5%minutes} or until crispy then remove from the pan
and keep to the side. Add the chicken to the (now empty) pan and cook for
~{5-8%minutes} until cooked through.

Mix the rice, beans, tomatoes, chorizo and onions with the cooked chicken and all but 1 tbsp
of the coriander. Make a dressing with the remaining zest and juice of the lime, 1/3 tsp of
@salt{}, some @pepper{} and 1 tbsp of @olive oil{} and mix with the rice salad.

> Tip: You can replace the olive oil with the pan juices from the chorizo and chicken.

Divide the salad between your bowls, sprinkle over the remaining coriander and tuck in!